reviews.text: Good quality food. soup, garlic bread, main course and coffee are all very good. Coffee is exceptional good for set meal. Garlic bread that goes with the soup is crispy and hot.

Tried this restaurant tonight for the first time. This is an extremely small restaurant trying to pass their dishes off as high quality western food. I must say upfront  I was somewhat disappointed by the food, the taste was no where near up to my expectations and especially for the moderately high prices they are charging. I ordered a lobster bisque and lamb chops. The soup was luke warm, too salty and small. The lamb chops were very average and borderline bland in taste. Utter disappointment.
The food taste good, and the service of the waiters were excellent.
Just soso
